4. Translate following sentences into propositional logic: -

I. If the machine is on, then the light is on, but the light is not on.

II. If Alice goes to the meeting, then Bob will go only if Charlie does not go.

III. If the code compiles and passes all tests, then it is ready for deployment; otherwise, it is not.

IV. The software is secure if and only if both encryption is enabled and authentication is required.

V. If either the firewall fails or the antivirus is disabled, then the system is vulnerable, but the antivirus is not disabled.
